					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up near the <hi rend="italic">dhvajastaṁbha</hi> of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1537 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1458, Durmukhi, Māgha śu. 12, Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1537 A.D., January 22.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the grant of the village Mārēḍumānipale <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Hanumantapuram in Būdigumma-sthalam in Kumdurppi-sīma included in Rāyadurga, to the temple of Hanumanta by Veṅkaṭādri, son of Dēvadāsu, the agent of Bayyappa-nāyaka, for the merit of the king and the chief.</p>						

						</summary>
